  "summary": "Remote Code Execution via unsafe deserialization in example-lib",
  "details": "A critical vulnerability was discovered in example-lib that allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via crafted serialized data. The vulnerability exists in the `deserialize()` function which does not properly validate input before processing.\n\n## Impact\n\nThis vulnerability affects all versions from 2.0.0 to 2.5.9. Attackers can exploit this to execute arbitrary code in the context of the application.\n\n## Remediation\n\nUpgrade to version 2.6.0 or later, which includes proper input validation.",
